    "Inspecting 10% of the answers reveals models often approach the task by analytical derivations but soon revert to heuristics as complexity increases, e.g., known properties, structure-based approximations.",
    "ConclusionWe evaluated LLMs graph reasoners under symmetry transformations and unseen spectral tasks.",
    "We decomposed serializations into three axes of variation: (i) node labeling, (ii) edge encoding, and (iii) syntax.",
    "We found that fine-tuning reduces sensitivity to node labeling, although mostly reflecting performance enhancement rather than true invariance.",
    "Also, we observed edge orderings to dictate computation paths, altering algorithmic difficulty and impacting performance."
